~ go
???: [wait=3.0]Now that that's over with, let's get you to your new home. 
???: You'll be staying at the Shopkeeper's house, on account of your Gift. He's Gifted himself, and I'm sure he's better suited to explain how it works than any of us are.
???: He's been in need of an apprentice since forever, anyway. 
???: That's his house. Just knock and tell him you're the Gifted newcomer the Elders mentioned, and that Joan sent you. He'll know what to do.
Joan: Farewell. May the Goddess guide your every step. 
- Goodbye, Joan. 
	You get to the Shopkeeper's house and knock. As soon as your knuckles touch the wood the door opens. He's been expecting you. 
	Shopkeeper: Hello there. I know who you are and why you're here. No need to get into it right now. We've got time.
	Shopkeeper: That there's your room. I've readied a change of clothes and a warm bath for you. Throw your own clothes in the fireplace once you're done.
	Shopkeeper: Get some sleep. Tomorrow we wake early. Lots of work to be done.
	Shopkeeper: I'm guessing you've got loads of questions for me. Don't worry, I'll answer each and every one of them, as best I can. 
	Shopkeeper: But now, my daughter, Sarah, is fast asleep. She's been helping me out all day and I'd hate for us to wake her up. 
	Shopkeeper: Good night. I'll see you in the morning.
	- Alright then. => END
	- Thank you. Good night. => END
